    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# YouTube Comment Analyzer\\n\",\"**NLP Project 74 of 100** — Analyze sentiment, toxicity, and feature requests in YouTube comments.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Process and clean user-generated content.\\n\",\"2. Apply sentiment analysis to social media comments.\\n\",\"3. Extract feature requests and feedback themes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, re, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nfrom sklearn.cluster import KMeans\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nSEED = 42; rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Synthetic YouTube comments\\ncomment_templates = {\\n    'positive': ['Great video!','Love this content','Very helpful tutorial','Best explanation ever','Keep making these!'] * 20,\\n    'negative': ['Waste of time','This is wrong','Terrible audio quality','Clickbait title','Disliked and unsubscribed'] * 10,\\n    'feature_request': ['Can you make a video about Python?','Please cover Docker next','Do a tutorial on React','Would love to see AWS content','Make more beginner content'] * 8,\\n    'question': ['How do I install this?','What version are you using?','Does this work on Mac?','Can you share the code?','When is the next video?'] * 12,\\n}\\nrows = []\\nfor sentiment, comments in comment_templates.items():\\n    for c in comments:\\n        rows.append({'comment': c, 'category': sentiment})\\ndf = pd.DataFrame(rows).sample(frac=1, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\nprint(f'Shape: {df.shape}'); print(df['category'].value_counts())\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Sentiment Distribution\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,4))\\ndf['category'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[0], color='steelblue', edgecolor='black')\\naxes[0].set_title('Comment Categories'); axes[0].tick_params(axis='x',rotation=30)\\ndf['comment_len'] = df['comment'].str.len()\\ndf.boxplot(column='comment_len', by='category', ax=axes[1])\\naxes[1].set_title('Comment Length by Category'); plt.suptitle('')\\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Topic Clustering\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=2000, stop_words='english')\\nX = tfidf.fit_transform(df['comment'])\\nkm = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=SEED, n_init=10)\\ndf['cluster'] = km.fit_predict(X)\\n\\nterms = tfidf.get_feature_names_out()\\nfor i in range(4):\\n    top = [terms[j] for j in km.cluster_centers_[i].argsort()[-5:][::-1]]\\n    print(f'Cluster {i}: {top}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Actionable Insights\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fr = df[df['category']=='feature_request']['comment'].tolist()\\nprint('Feature Requests:')\\nfor r in fr[:5]: print(f'  • {r}')\\nprint(f'\\\\nNegative feedback rate: {(df[\\\"category\\\"]==\\\"negative\\\").mean():.1%}')\\nprint(f'Feature requests: {(df[\\\"category\\\"]==\\\"feature_request\\\").mean():.1%}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **YouTube comments can be automatically categorized** into feedback types.\\n\",\"- **Feature requests are valuable signals** for content planning.\\n\",\"- **Negative feedback analysis helps improve** content quality.\\n\",\"- **For production, use YouTube Data API** to collect real comments.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
